<h2><span id="What_is_the_best_angle_grinder">What is the best angle grinder?</span></h2>
<p>A state-of-the-art angle grinder should become the number one tool among others in a tool set of a skillful craftsman or a contractor. It is proved by a high versatility as it can be used for numerous tasks. They include cutting at any angle, grinding, sanding and polishing of various materials.</p>
<p>The advanced options can be fitted with multiple common accessories, which together with a powerful motor can deliver speed up to 11000 RPM, making this tool suitable for a vast variety of applications.</p>
<p>Besides, the good angle grinder ensures total safety of an operator which uses it with no fatigue at all. Thus, the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Makita-XAG16Z-Cut-Off-Angle-Grinder/dp/B0794J7TNT/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;linkId=712b2a3d6ddae585d55fdb5a5a34bf88&amp;language=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MAKITA XAG16Z</a> is in the forefront of my considerations when looking for the best angle grinder.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Makita-XAG16Z-Cut-Off-Angle-Grinder/dp/B0794J7TNT/ref=as_li_ss_il?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=li3&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;linkId=aa0c0ee73434f64913d4534ba2cc5bc2&amp;language=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img class="aligncenter" title="Makita XAG16Z 18V LXT BL 4-1/2”/ 5&quot; Cut-Off/Angle Grinder: buy" src="//ws-na.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?_encoding=UTF8&amp;ASIN=B0794J7TNT&amp;Format=_SL200_&amp;ID=AsinImage&amp;MarketPlace=US&amp;ServiceVersion=20070822&amp;WS=1&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;language=en_US" alt="Makita XAG16Z 18V LXT BL 4-1/2”/ 5&quot; Cut-Off/Angle Grinder: photo" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>Why have I chosen this model? Firstly, I love the opportunity of its mobility and freedom from any cords that can be really annoying during operation. It comes with 18V lithium-ion batteries that proved their reliability even for the continuous operations. This model features a brushless motor which enhances the efficiency and stability of operation as well as contributes to longer service life of the tool, in general.</p>
<p>One of the most distinguished features of the <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Makita-XAG16Z-Cut-Off-Angle-Grinder/dp/B0794J7TNT/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;linkId=712b2a3d6ddae585d55fdb5a5a34bf88&amp;language=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MAKITA XAG16Z</a> is its variable speed control function which is an outstanding one among other cordless counterparts. Due to this feature it can be adjusted from 3000 up to 85000 RPM, depending on the application, enhancing the accuracy and the overall quality of you works.</p>
<p>I like its safety features which consist of anti-feedback technology, soft start function and electronic protection system designed for control of the correct motor functioning and optimization of battery energy use.</p>
<h2><span id="Types_of_the_angle_grinders">Types of the angle grinders</span></h2>
<h3>Corded</h3>
<p>Corded models are run by the standard residential 120 V power outlet. Typically they are more powerful, but also bigger and heavier in comparison with the cordless models. The main advantage of the corded angle grinders is in their power capacity. That is they deliver enough power for any project, including the heavy-duty applications. Besides they are offered at comparatively affordable prices with a wide power range options. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/DEWALT-DWE402-2-Inch-11-Amp-Grinder/dp/B00RVZ7DNO/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;linkId=eeb035073f51d59468434076ea68737c&amp;language=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">DEWALT DWE402</a> features enough power and reliability to be considered first among other corded options.</p><div class=\'code-block code-block-5\' style=\'margin: 8px 0; clear: both;\'>
<amp-ad width="300" height="250"
    type="yandex"
    data-block-id="R-A-443739-12"
    data-html-access-allowed="true">
</amp-ad></div>

<p>The downside of application of the corded angle grinders is that your mobility during operation will be restricted by necessity to connect them to the power outlet. Surely, you can use an extension cord, but still it is not endless. It will constantly get in the way during operation thus endangering safety of an operator. Besides, there is a risk of its damage by the accessories used during the process.</p>
<h3>Cordless</h3>
<p><a href="https://tehno.guru/best-cordless-angle-grinder/">Cordless angle grinders</a> are free from any cords, but still their runtime is restricted by the life of the battery which should be recharged periodically. The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Makita-XAG16Z-Cut-Off-Angle-Grinder/dp/B0794J7TNT/ref=as_li_ss_tl?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=ll1&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;linkId=712b2a3d6ddae585d55fdb5a5a34bf88&amp;language=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MAKITA XAG16Z</a> is a bright example of the most advanced and high-performance cordless options available on the market.</p>
<p>Find the in-depth review of the best cordless angle grinders, and the features to be considered when looking for a battery-powered model here.</p>
<h3>Pneumatic</h3>
<p>The pneumatic angle grinders are lightweight options which run by an air compressor. Pneumatic models are commonly used in the metal-working industry. Also they will be indispensable at the job sites with a high humidity and for the most heavy-duty applications.</p>
<p>As the compressed air is the power source here, such angle grinders shall be connected to a pneumatic pipeline or a compressor of an appropriate capacity, depending on a type of your application.</p>
<p>The main advantage of the pneumatic models is that they are capable to operate under the conditions of an increased humidity with no risk to safety. Besides, the risk of their overheating is reduced to the minimum, even in case of an intensive or a heavy-duty operation. This is the best type for contractors who already operate various pneumatic tools, as it will help them to provide a sufficient workload for the compressor they use.</p>
<h2><span id="Features_to_be_considered_when_looking_for_an_angle_grinder_Buyers_Guide">Features to be considered when looking for an angle grinder | Buyer’s Guide</span></h2>
<h3>Motor power</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Makita-XAG16Z-Cut-Off-Angle-Grinder/dp/B0794J7TNT/ref=as_li_ss_il?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=li3&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;linkId=3795634b4f78a13b4a564464774d00b6&amp;language=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img class="aligncenter" title="Makita XAG16Z: buy" src="//ws-na.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?_encoding=UTF8&amp;ASIN=B0794J7TNT&amp;Format=_SL200_&amp;ID=AsinImage&amp;MarketPlace=US&amp;ServiceVersion=20070822&amp;WS=1&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;language=en_US" alt="Makita XAG16Z: photo"  border="0" /></a></p>
<p>The input power of a standard angle grinder is between 110 and 230 volts. The rated output power of these tools varies from 650 up to 2700 W and depends on a disk diameter to be used. Accordingly, the angle grinders with bigger diameter disks are equipped with more powerful motors. The latter provide enough force at the cutting edge to process effectively a workpiece.</p>
<p>Hence, the power ratings of your angle grinder should be selected considering the jobs you are going to fulfill mostly. If, let’s say, you are going to deal with heavy-duty tasks like metal cutting, you need to pick up a tool which delivers plenty of power. However, you should be ready to pay extra for this.</p>
<h3>Rotation speed</h3>
<p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00009YUHX/ref=as_li_ss_il?ie=UTF8&amp;linkCode=li3&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;linkId=470353336480cb9b1729615d5d721797&amp;language=en_US" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img class="aligncenter" title="DEWALT D28499X: buy" src="//ws-na.amazon-adsystem.com/widgets/q?_encoding=UTF8&amp;ASIN=B00009YUHX&amp;Format=_SL200_&amp;ID=AsinImage&amp;MarketPlace=US&amp;ServiceVersion=20070822&amp;WS=1&amp;tag=tehno-guru-20&amp;language=en_US" alt="DEWALT D28499X: photo" border="0" /></a></p>
<p>The rotation speed of the angle grinder depends on the diameter of a disk; the bigger the attached disk, the slower the tool. The speed of the angle grinders is measured in RPM, or rotations per minute. It can be in the range from 5,000 to 13,000 RPM.</p>
<p>However, faster speeds can be effective and destructive at the same time. You should always set the right speed for the materials to be processed, by consulting the manuals and recommendations of the manufacturers. Besides, skills and expertise of an operator would be no less crucial in obtaining the desired results.</p>
<h3>Safety features</h3>
<p>Most advanced angle grinders are offered with the features like soft start, restart protection and speed setting systems which contribute to convenience and safety of an operator.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Slow Start.</strong> Even if you are going to work at high speed rates, it would be more preferable and safe to ramping it up slowly. A smooth start will enhance the durability of the tool in general, as it serves as a motor protection and anti-vibration feature, which is especially useful during long-run operations.</li>
<li><strong>Restart protection.</strong> During extended construction work there is a risk of a sudden power shutdown which can occur for various reasons. The restart protection feature eliminates the risk of an unintended start when the power supply is back. As usually an operator would leave the tool aside, without checking the position of the switch. Such protection will also prevent the grinder from restarting if it gets overheated. The angle grinders with such function can be restarted only after trigger switching-off with further intended restart.</li>
<li><strong>Speed setting.</strong> The speed can be varied with the help of the wheel located on the tool body. Cheap angle grinders are commonly offered without this feature. But as practice shows, this feature is very useful when tackling particular jobs which require higher accuracy in cutting or grinding. For instance, if you need to grind off any paintwork, an intensive rotation may lead to surface scorching.</li>
</ul>
