<h3>Battery capacity (cordless models)</h3>
<p>The battery is the most essential part of any cordless angle grinder. It can ensure a long runtime of your tool. For this reason, you should select those models with lithium-ion batteries. The tools with such batteries weigh less and can be operated longer than their counterparts. Besides, recharging time of the lithium-ion batteries is the shortest in comparison with other current options.</p>
<p>And pay attention that nowadays the majority of brands use the same batteries as the rest of other cordless tools from their range. So, if you have any tool of a particular manufacturer, you may exchange the same batteries from one tool to another.</p>
<h3>Pressure and air flow (pneumatic models)</h3>
<p>As the pneumatic angle grinders are powered by the compressed air, the question about its amount and pressure arises. In order to ensure a reliable operation of the pneumatic model during extended periods, the compressor which is capable to produce from 5 to 8 CFM at 90 PSI would be a right choice.</p>
