<h2><span id="FAQ">FAQ</span></h2>
<p><em>What can I do with an angle grinder?<br />
</em>With the use of different wheels attached to the angle grinder, you can grind, cut, sand and polish various materials. It is capable to tackle even the most challenging tasks like processing ferrous and non-ferrous metals and their alloys, natural and artificial stone, concrete and bricks, etc.</p>
<p><em>What is the best angle grinder wheel for cutting metal &amp; for concrete?</em><br />
Grit discs are the commonly used options for metal cutting. They are thinner in comparison with other grinding discs. But the thinnest disks are designed to cut the soft metal only; otherwise a high risk of injury appears. There are grit disks suitable for cutting ferrous metals, stainless steel and non-ferrous metals. However, it is better to use a grit disk designed for a specific material.</p>
<p>Diamond discs are versatile and more advance options in comparison with the above mentioned. This type of accessory is suitable for cutting concrete, tile, and marble, including ferrous and non-ferrous metals. Such cutting blades are quite expensive but demonstrate high-performance at the same time. It is recommended to use such disks when cutting reinforced concrete, as they can handle the rebar and nails. Besides, as the practice shows, they are safer to use.</p>
<p><em>How to remove an angle grinder disk?<br />
</em>Typically the angle grinders come with the manuals with the specification of the disk removal procedure.</p>
<p>The following steps should be followed to remove a disk safely:</p>
<ol>
<li>Disconnect the power. If you deal with a cordless model, remove the battery pack from the tool.</li>
<li>Press a side lock-on button to hold the disk in place.</li>
<li>With the help of a spanner wrench (which is typically in the scope of supply) unscrew a nut and loosen the disk. You should spin the spanner in the direction of disk rotation.</li>
<li>Remove the disk to be replaced.</li>
<li>Install a new disk manually or with the help of the same spanner.</li>
</ol>
<h2><span id="How_to_use_an_angle_grinder_safely">How to use an angle grinder safely?<em><br />
</em></span></h2>
<p>You should not forget about safety precautions while working with an angle grinder. That is why I’ve prepared a list of the safety rules to be followed during operation of your angle grinder.</p>
<ol>
<li>Always wear safety goggles and ear plugs or use a protective shield.</li>
<li>Use the wheels of the suitable size and type when processing a particular material.</li>
<li>Use the tool only for the purposes according to its specifications specified in the manual.</li>
<li>Light and small workpieces should be clamped or secured.</li>
<li>It’s better to hold the angle grinder from the side, thus preventing any injury due to a possible kickback of the tool during operation.</li>
<li>It is forbidden to be in the close proximity to a disk blade as it is the most dangerous and not covered area.</li>
</ol>
<p>The tool will serve you long with no risks to personal safety, if you follow the above mentioned recommendations.</p>
<h2><span id="What_is_an_angle_grinder">What is an angle grinder?<em><br />
</em></span></h2>
<p>Grinding and polishing are highly applicable during processing of internal and external surfaces of various workpieces of different shapes and materials. Such operations usually result in obtaining the smooth surfaces with a low roughness. An angle grinder with the suitable disc can replace multiple tools and tackle the most fatiguing, labour intensive jobs in a quicker and easier manner. That is why, such grinders are the main tools obligatory used to succeed in those projects. Besides, it can be used for cutting and other applications about which you will learn a bit later in this article.</p>
<p>The main accessory of this tool is a wheel attached to the tool body at a right angle and rotating on a spindle shaft at high rates of speed. Primarily this tool is designed for grinding and cleaning of surfaces, rather than smoothing. However if, for instance, the angle grinder is equipped with a cutting disk, it will be capable to cut such hard materials like rebar, angles, pipes and hollow sections.</p>
<p>Thus, the angle grinder is a convenient and versatile tool which is widely used both at the large production facilities and at the home workshops for smaller DIY jobs.</p>
<p>If you continue to read this guide, you will learn about main features, principles of operation and specifications of the angle grinders. In this regard you will be able to select the right option, among the widest range offered on the market, satisfying your needs to the utmost.<!-- mishanin test --></p>
